1 Affairs, or any other federally chartered veterans' service organization.
2 Other organizations, including but not limited to the Kentucky Department
3 of Veterans' Affairs, a local veterans' service organization, and other
4 federally chartered veterans' service organizations may be able to provide
5 you with this service free of charge. Products or services offered by this
6 business are not necessarily endorsed by any of these organizations. You
7 may qualify for other veterans' benefits beyond the benefits for which you
8 are receiving services here."
9 (b) The written disclosure in paragraph (a) of this subsection shall appear in at
10 least twelve (12) point font and shall appear in a readily noticeable and
11 identifiable place in the person's agreement with the individual seeking
12 services. The individual shall verbally acknowledge understanding of the
13 oral disclosure and sign the document in which the written disclosure
14 appears to represent understanding of these provisions. The person offering
15 services shall retain a copy of the written disclosure while providing
16 veterans' benefits services for compensation to the individual and for at
17 least one (1) year after the date on which the service relations terminate.
18 (9) A violation of this section shall constitute an unfair, false, misleading, or
19 deceptive act or practice in the conduct of trade or commerce under KRS 367.170.
20 (10) Notwithstanding this section, an attorney or law firm seeking to receive
21 compensation for advising, assisting, or consulting any individual with any
22 veterans' benefits matter shall be governed by the limitations set forth in 38
23 C.F.R. sec. 14.636.
